│                                                                                            │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                            │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                │
│ The crash is an assertion failure in LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF(), which      │
│ compares the VPlan-based cost model's chosen VF against the legacy cost model's chosen VF. │
│ The assertion allows disagreement only if the VPlan contains additional simplifications    │
│ not accounted for by the legacy model. In this reproducer, the assertion fires, meaning    │
│ the VPlan-based and legacy cost models disagree and the code does not recognize any        │
│ additional simplifications.                                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                    │
│ The log shows the assertion at LoopVectorize.cpp:7360: "VPlan cost model and legacy cost   │
│ model disagreed". The debug-only run doesn't print more, but the first transformation      │
│ point is computeBestVF where it calculates cost using cost(VPlan, VF) and compares with    │
│ selectVectorizationFactor (legacy). The path then calls                                    │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications to decide whether disagreement is acceptable.        │
│                                                                                            │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                    │
│ Looking at planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(VPlan &Plan, ElementCount VF,             │
│ VPCostContext &CostCtx, Loop *TheLoop, LoopVectorizationCostModel &CM), the function tries │
│ to detect if VPlan has simplifications by checking instructions in the original loop not   │
│ represented in the VPlan nor skipped by CostCtx.                                           │
│ The relevant code:                                                                         │
│   return any_of(TheLoop->blocks(), [...](Instruction &I) {                                 │
│     if (isa<PHINode>(&I)) return false;                                                    │
│     return !SeenInstrs.contains(&I) &&                                                     │
│            !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true) &&                                       │
│            !CM.canTruncateToMinimalBitwidth(&I, VF);                                       │
│   });                                                                                      │
│ Note skipCostComputation is called with a hardcoded 'true' instead of reflecting the       │
│ actual VF's vector/scalar nature (VF.isVector()). This mismatched parameter can lead to    │
│ incorrect classification of which instructions are skipped by the VPlan-based cost model.  │
│ As a result, planContainsAdditionalSimplifications may return false even when there are    │
│ extra simplifications, or vice versa, causing the assertion to fire unnecessarily when the │
│ two cost models disagree legitimately.                                                     │
│ Given the function signature includes VF, it's clear the intent is to use VF to decide     │
│ vector context. The hardcoded 'true' is a bug.                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                                  │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                    │
│ - Lines: 7288-7289                                                                         │
│ - Change:                                                                                  │
│   From:                                                                                    │
│     !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true) &&                                              │
│   To:                                                                                      │
│     !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, VF.isVector()) &&                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ This uses the actual ElementCount VF to determine whether the cost context is vector or    │
│ scalar for skipping cost computation, aligning planContainsAdditionalSimplifications with  │
│ the intended behavior.                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                             │
│ The assertion failure arises because planContainsAdditionalSimplifications erroneously     │
│ uses a constant 'true' for vector context, leading to incorrect detection of extra         │
│ simplifications and thus not allowing valid disagreements between the VPlan and legacy     │
│ cost models. Replacing 'true' with VF.isVector() ensures the check accurately reflects the │
│ vectorization factor under consideration. This should prevent the spurious assertion and   │
│ allow the VPlan-based cost model to legitimately differ when extra simplifications are     │
│ present.                                                                                   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                            │
│                                                                                            │
